<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  exportOptions.plist — UNSIGNED IPA export for the SideStore / AltStore model.

  Pose Deck is distributed via SideStore, which re-signs the app *on device*
  using a free Apple ID + a self-hosted Anisette server (ARCHITECTURE.md §9/§10,
  PROJECT_PLAN.md M7). The CI artifact is therefore intentionally UNSIGNED: there
  is no Apple Developer team, no provisioning profile, and no signing identity on
  the GitHub macOS runner.

  How this is used (see .github/workflows/ios.yml, job `archive-ipa`):
    1. `xcodebuild archive ... CODE_SIGNING_ALLOWED=NO` produces an unsigned
       .xcarchive (the app binary is built but not codesigned).
    2. The workflow PREFERS the manual Payload/ zip approach to turn that archive
       into PoseDeck.ipa, because `xcodebuild -exportArchive` frequently refuses
       to export when there is no signing identity / team. This plist exists as
       the *documented fallback* path for `-exportArchive` and to make the intent
       explicit; if a future Xcode tolerates an unsigned `development` export it
       will be used with `CODE_SIGNING_ALLOWED=NO`.

  Keys:
    method            development — closest to the "sideload to my own devices"
                      intent. (ad-hoc also works; both are fine because the
                      artifact is re-signed on device anyway.)
    signingStyle      manual — do NOT let Xcode try automatic signing (it would
                      reach for an Apple ID / team that does not exist in CI).
    teamID            empty — no Apple Developer team. Leave blank.
    stripSwiftSymbols false — keep symbols; SideStore/AltStore handle the rest.
    compileBitcode    false — bitcode is deprecated; never enabled here.
    destination       export — write the .ipa to disk (not upload).
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>method</key>
    <string>development</string>
    <key>signingStyle</key>
    <string>manual</string>
    <key>teamID</key>
    <string></string>
    <key>stripSwiftSymbols</key>
    <false/>
    <key>compileBitcode</key>
    <false/>
    <key>destination</key>
    <string>export</string>
</dict>
</plist>
